  "chunk_index": 15,
  "summary": "Colston Lindstrom warns Hester Aigle that she cannot trust anyone, asserting that the killer is someone within their own social circle. Following a recent incident where a visitor clarified that Jacqueline is not the murderer, Colston advises Hester to be wary of Mary, her father Leo, and Gwendolyn Vance. He suggests that Hester leave the house for her own safety, specifically mentioning Dr. Calgary, though Hester defends the doctor. Frustrated by the tension, Hester expresses a wish that Dr. Calgary had never visited.\n\nElsewhere, Leo Aigle finishes signing letters for Gwendolyn Vance. Gwendolyn discusses Leo's upcoming trip to Rome and Siena to examine archives mentioned by Cardinal Machirini, suggesting he would be better off away from the current situation. Gwendolyn implies that Dr. Calgary might be the killer due to his terrible temperament, but Leo expresses doubt; he notes that while the doctor attacks younger children, he seemed afraid of Rachel. Gwendolyn privately contemplates that Rachel’s commanding and \"always right\" nature might have motivated someone to kill her with a poker.\n\nWhen Gwendolyn asks to move their planned March wedding to an earlier date, Leo refuses, insisting they must not rush and must be \"sure.\" This refusal leaves Gwendolyn upset and trembling. After Kirsten Lindstrom leaves them following a brief visit with tea, Leo reflects on his first meeting with Rachel Constable at a social club in London's East End, remembering her earnestness and her unwavering belief in doing good.",
